org.apache.flink.streaming.api.datastream

Class GroupedDataStream<OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.streaming.api.datastream.DataStream<OUT>
      • org.apache.flink.streaming.api.datastream.GroupedDataStream<OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    OUT - The output type of the GroupedDataStream.

    public class GroupedDataStream<OUT>
extends DataStream<OUT>
    A GroupedDataStream represents a DataStream which has been partitioned by the given key in the values. Operators like reduce(org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.ReduceFunction<OUT>), #batchReduce etc. can be applied on the GroupedDataStream to get additional functionality by the grouping.

      • reduce

        public SingleOutputStreamOperator<OUT,?> reduce(ReduceFunction<OUT> reducer)
        Applies a reduce transformation on the grouped data stream grouped on by the given key position. The ReduceFunction will receive input values based on the key value. Only input values with the same key will go to the same reducer.The user can also extend RichReduceFunction to gain access to other features provided by the RichFuntion interface.
        Overrides:
        reduce in class DataStream<OUT>
        Parameters:
        reducer - The ReduceFunction that will be called for every element of the input values with the same key.
        Returns:
        The transformed DataStream.
